1 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 5009.7 of Title 63, unless there
3 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 A. The Oklahoma Health Care Authority shall seek any necessary
5 federal approval to provide coverage for nutrition supports under
6 the state Medicaid program for the purpose of implementing Food is
7 Medicine programs as provided by this section.
8 B. Food is Medicine programs shall be designed to improve
9 health outcomes for Medicaid members with nutrition-related chronic
10 diseases through nutrition services and to reduce the need for
11 medical care.
12 C. Nutrition services covered under the state Medicaid program
13 may include, but are not limited to:
14 1. Case management;
15 2. Nutrition counseling;
16 3. Meals or pantry stocking;
17 4. Nutrition prescriptions; and
18 5. Grocery provisions.
19 D. Wherever feasible, the Authority and contracted entities
20 under the state Medicaid program shall prioritize the inclusion of
21 community-based organizations and local growers to support the
22 purchase of locally grown food in nutrition prescriptions.
