1 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 5-147.2 of Title 70, unless
3 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 The State Department of Education shall provide, to schools who
5 apply for grants under the Oklahoma Farm to School Program Act
6 codified at Section 5-60.1 et seq. of Title 2 of the Oklahoma
7 Statutes, technical assistance with applying for grants and
8 administering programs that expand student access to fresh, healthy
9 food.
10 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
11 SECTION 5. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
12 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
13 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
14 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
